attachments.title: Google virtual reality -- Cardboard recycled into something you actually want
attachments.text: Google working on a new virtual-reality addon, which will replace the “Cardboard” silliness, say deep-throat sources. The journalistic gobbledygook of “people familiar with its plans” popped up to leak Google’s VR future...
attachments.fallback: Computerworld: Google virtual reality -- Cardboard recycled into something you actually want

text: I really want to get our wall concept loaded into Cardboard so our clients can experience it at different heights, etc. and get a feel for scale
Off-the-shelf solutions are meh at best

Sadly, no. I'm going to reach out to Josh at Google to see if he can connect us with some folks in their skunk works team that does some really cool cardboard work. Barring that, InsiteVR looks good enough.
<@U0HPGQ4KH>: I have an account on InsiteVR now. If you can generate a 360 panorama from SketchUp, we can view it. Can’t do walkthroughs ($$ account for that), but we can at least play.
Ok. Let me find out of how to do a 360 panorama.
